        public java.lang.String getHashedSaltedPassword()
        Returns:
        The salted and bcrypt hashed output. Do not directly compare it with the output of a hash to verify a login. Instead, use Authentication.authenticate(String, String).

      • setHashedSaltedPassword

        public void setHashedSaltedPassword(java.lang.String rawPassword)
        Parameters:
        rawPassword - a raw password string. Will be hashed and salted using bcrypt, before storing into the database. By default, uses 10 rounds of hashing.
